<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="910" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-07T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 7, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4141. Your 5278, December 6. As special subjects that should be brought
                            up at the conference were mentioned: Treatment of submarines and
                            airships; destruction of neutral prizes; granting of asylum to prizes;
                            issuance of black lists by the belligerents; and the economic situation
                            after the war. In choosing subjects for discussion, the guiding
                            principle was to avoid the appearance of taking sides with either of the
                            belligerent groups. The question of mediation was excluded from the
                            program.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>